trans-unit.source: Property descriptors present in objects come in two main flavors: data descriptors and accessor descriptors. A data descriptor is a property that has a value, which may or may not be writable. An accessor descriptor is a property described by a getter-setter pair of functions. A descriptor must be one of these two flavors; it cannot be both.
trans-unit.target: 对象中存在的属性描述符有两种主要形式：数据描述符和访问器描述符。甲数据描述符是具有值，其可以是或可以不是可写的一个属性。一个访问器描述符是通过吸气剂制定者对功能所描述的属性。描述符必须是这两种形式之一。不能两者兼有。

trans-unit.source: Returns a promise that either fulfills when all of the promises in the iterable argument have fulfilled or rejects as soon as one of the promises in the iterable argument rejects. If the returned promise fulfills, it is fulfilled with an array of the values from the fulfilled promises in the same order as defined in the iterable. If the returned promise rejects, it is rejected with the reason from the first promise in the iterable that rejected. This method can be useful for aggregating results of multiple promises.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个承诺,它要么是在所有iterable参数中的承诺都实现时实现,要么是在iterable参数中的一个承诺拒绝时拒绝。如果返回的承诺实现了,那么它将被一个数组实现,这个数组中的值与iterable参数中定义的顺序相同。如果返回的承诺被拒绝,那么就会用iterable中第一个被拒绝的承诺的理由来拒绝。这个方法对于聚合多个承诺的结果很有用。

trans-unit.source: Returns a promise that fulfills or rejects as soon as one of the promises in the iterable fulfills or rejects, with the value or reason from that promise.
trans-unit.target: 返回一个实现或拒绝的承诺,只要iterable中的一个承诺实现或拒绝,就返回该承诺的值或理由。
